Album_Description:
The Spectre” is a song is initially released as a typical single in September 2017 – by itself, a remake of his classical track, “Spectre” in 2015, originally released under NoCopyrightSounds.

In September 2023, the track was adopted in a widely-circulated meme dubbed the “Smurf cat,” or its original Russian name “Shailushai” (Шайлушай; “little scoundrel”) in videos depicting a realistic artwork of the popular cartoon characters known The Smurfs, with the song used in the background. This prompted Walker to release a remix collection, which features a new official slowed down version (which is frequently used by the meme, albeit being made unofficially), bundled up with the original track and its sped-up version originally released in July 2022.

Album_Description: Live Fast (Japan Exclusive)" is a compelling album by Norwegian DJ and producer Alan Walker, released exclusively in Japan on August 9, 2019. This album showcases a collection of eight tracks, blending electronic and dance-pop genres, which highlight Walker's signature synth-heavy and melody-driven style. The album features a mix of solo tracks and collaborations with various artists, offering a dynamic range of sounds that cater to both energetic and emotional moods.
